title: Robb sticks with India FTA aim by year end
text:
Sun, Jul 12, 2015, 2:34 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Robb sticks with India FTA aim by year end AAP – 3 hours ago Print 
It's a big task, but Trade Minister Andrew Robb still believes he can secure a free trade agreement with India by the end of the year. 
He said it will have a very strong emphasis on services and investment to support India's growing manufacturing base. 
"We really have another China in prospect ... it will be another key plank in the post-mining boom adjustment strategy that we have got as a government," Mr Robb told Sky News on Sunday. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Industry group backs Watermark mine AAP
